AUDIO: 'another customer in. Um so, it\'s it\'s something I can bring back to the team. I guess I\'ll put it that way. With no immediate plans that I know of. Um the second question\'s from Life of Code. Ask him about spam filters, flags IPs, and how to maintain'

[40:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quality to prevent it. I got a lot to talk about with domain reputation and deliverability, so I don\'t want to go too long, but there\'s a lot there. But uh yeah, we\'ve done I\'ve done some content on it in the past, so I\'d'

[40:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'probably encourage them to to look at that. Um but generally speaking, like I think devs just assume like if you get the throughput, then it\'s going to land in the inbox, and there\'s a lot that can go into to landing there.'

[41:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Right now, basically uh Gmail especially, and they\'re really the ones who own email in a in a lot of senses, they mostly care about your domain reputation, not your IP reputation. That doesn\'t mean that IP doesn\'t matter at all. Um we do our job'

[41:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to make sure our IPs are you know, are really healthy, but it\'s your domain that matters, so where you\'re sending from. And uh think about it like a post office. If you just show up one day and'

[41:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'drop 100,000 letters on the desk, they\'re going to say like who is this guy, you know, and and not trust you. You really have to build reputation trust, and it it can take a little bit to build, and you can lose it very'

[41:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'quickly. Um and so, you have to really put in a bunch of safeguards for yourselves. So, that\'s everything from like making sure that you um like send from a subdomain, so that way if you have issues with your domain,'

[41:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can move it to another subdomain without having effect every single sending on your on your whole platform. So, there\'s like some basic things like that. Making sure you include unsubscribe links and things that are not merely like transactional emails'

[42:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around like off or things like that. So, there\'s a lot of guidance there. But every time an email comes in your uh email inbox, the email inbox that\'s receiving that, Gmail, Yahoo, Outlook, whatever, they are they are looking at'

[42:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that using their own proprietary set of like filters. So, they don\'t tell anyone what that is cuz if they did, then all we would get is spam emails. So, they\'re trying to they\'re trying to read a lot of signals that has everything to do with how often you\'re sending.'

[42:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Um there\'s some authentication things like DMARC and SPF and uh DKIM, which that\'s that\'s a whole set of acronyms I just threw out there. Um so, like you said, there\'s a lot of weird comp complexity around email. But, generally'

[42:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'speaking, that mindset will really help developers to think, "Okay, do I look like a trusted sender? Am I sending to people who have already opted in to receive this?" So, like we don\'t allow cold emails on Resend. Uh you have to'

[42:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have actual consent to send to people. Um so, there\'s a lot of basics like that that if you follow the basics, you send to people who only want to receive it, you send in a trusted way, not just dumping thousands of emails uh immediately like that.'

[43:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And then you pay attention to basic uh best practices. Like, there\'s not like specific words not to use, but generally speaking, like your links should be the same as the sending domain. Your images should be the same as the sending'

[43:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'domain. Don\'t use like spammy type words. Um and a lot of times what you\'ll find is that Gmail in particular will tell you, "Hey, this isn\'t spam for this reason." And you can adjust the content and see how that affects it. When you send with Resend, we also show deliverability'

[43:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'insights for every email you send, and that\'s a part to educate you. So, every email you send, you can look at the emails table, uh look at that particular email, and it gives you insights of like, "Hey, make sure you\'re doing all of these best practices." So, generally'

[43:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'speaking, if you think like that, "Hey, I\'m going to send in a way that\'s trustworthy, where people want to receive this, they\'ve opted in already, I\'m sending in a predictable pattern." Those are really the big mental things you have to think through. And then'

[43:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there\'s a lot of particulars that we can help you figure out as well. So, that\'s as brief an of an answers I can give about spam filters and deliverability and IP and domain reputation. Uh hopefully that was intelligible uh with all those acronyms.'

